ANALYSIS: 

DoS at 79.4% is solid. Published papers using PCA on NSL-KDD report 75-95% DoS DR.
Probe at 51.3% is acceptable. Probe attacks are slower and more varied.
R2L at 12.8% and U2R at 38.8% are poor — but this is a known, documented limitation of any anomaly detection approach on R2L/U2R. 
They're designed to look like normal traffic. Even supervised classifiers struggle with them.
